Description: Rim sherd of East Greek grey ware pottery dinos; dark grey fabric core sandwiched between beige margins, with mica inclusions; very worn dark grey slip and inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: Modern incised inscription on inside 'Hera' indicates findspot.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.042)
